  m_Name: CardSelectionTutorialDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  HintList:
  - 'This is the Card Selection Menu, where you to get choose from a selection of
    cards that are drawn <b>randomly</b> from your <b>Deck</b>.


    While the Card
    Selection Menu is open, you are in the <b>Planning Phase</b>. During this phase,
    time is <b>paused</b>, and neither you or your enemies will be able to move or
    act.'
  - 'You may <b>Left-Click</b> on any of the cards in the <b>Card Selection</b> area,
    which will then be sent to your <b>Card Magazine</b>.


    Your card magazine
    is a <b>first-in-first-out queue</b> of cards, where you may only use the first
    card within the magazine before being able to use the next.


    Due to this,
    <b>it is important to consider the order of your cards to make sure that you
    are able to use the right card at the right time.</b>'
  - "You may <b>Right-Click</b> any of the cards within the card selection panel
    in order to <b>lock the description panel in place</b>. <b>Right-Click</b> any
    card again to unlock it. \n\nHovering over some of the icons within the description
    panel may give you additional information.\n\nBe sure to <b>read the description
    of cards carefully</b> as understanding their effect is vital to your success!\n"
  - "The button right underneath the card magazine is the <b>Preview Stage</b> button.
    \n\nUse this button when you want to get a better look at the state of the stage
    before finishing your <b>Planning Phase</b>. \n"
  - When you're ready, click the big green tick box to load your card magazine, which
    closes the card selection menu and ends the current <b>Planning Phase</b>.
